msgid "DDs get +1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:20 app/data/cards.py:28 app/data/cards.py:44
msgid "When a DD is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:25
msgid "Interlinked Targeting Computer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:26
msgid ""
"Unlimited attack technology on Destroyers. Existing DDs instantly get the"
" ability to have Attack technology greater than their Hull Size because "
"of this card, but they still must be retrofitted with that technology "
"normally (Attack 2 or Attack 3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:33
msgid "Polytitanium Alloy"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:34
msgid "DDs cost 2 less."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:41
msgid "Long Lance Torpedo"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:42
msgid ""
"All of this player's DDs fire as B-Class instead of D-Class <mark class"
"=\"hl-blue\">(Alternate Empire DDs fire as B-Class instead of "
"C-Class)</mark>. This doesn't apply in terrain where they would fire as "
"E-Class (5.8)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:49
msgid "Central Computer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:50
msgid "CA and BC pay 1/2 maintenance (round down the total)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:57
msgid "Resupply Depot"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:58
msgid "BB and DN pay 1/2 maintenance (round down the total)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:65
msgid "Holodeck"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:66
msgid "CV and F pay 1/2 maintenance (round down the total)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:68 app/data/cards.py:1866 app/data/cards.py:1952
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-green\">CV or BV (MRB 3.6.2)</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:75
msgid "Cold Fusion Drive"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:76
msgid "Rs and SWs pay 1/2 maintenance (round down the total)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:83
msgid "Emissive Armor"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:84
msgid ""
"CAs take 1 extra hit to kill. However, their Hull Size does not increase "
"because of this card: it is still considered 2 (barring other card "
"effects). This does not help them against boarding attacks."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:86 app/data/cards.py:94
msgid "When a CA is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:91
msgid "Electronic Warfare Module"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:92
msgid "CAs get +1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:99
msgid "Microwarp Drive"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:100
msgid "BCs get +1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:102
msgid "When a BC is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:107
msgid "Combat Sensors"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:108
msgid "BBs get +1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:110
msgid "When a BB is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:115
msgid "Afterburners"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:116
msgid ""
"After researching Fighters, all of your Fighters get +1 on their Attack "
"when firing on ships with a Hull Size of 1 (or less, if playing with the "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Insectoids #43</span>)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:118 app/data/cards.py:126
msgid "When a Fighter is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:123
msgid "Photon Bomb"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:124
msgid ""
"After researching Fighters, all of your Fighters get +1 on their Attack "
"when firing on ships with a Hull Size greater than 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:131
msgid "Stim Packs"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:132
msgid "All Ground Units get +1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:134
msgid "In ground combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:139
msgid "Improved Crew's Quarters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:140
msgid "CAs cost 3 less."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:147
msgid "Phased Warp Coil"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:148
msgid "BCs cost 3 less."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:155
msgid "Advanced Ordnance Storage System"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:156
msgid "BBs cost 4 less."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:163
msgid "The Captain's Chair"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:164
msgid "DNs cost 4 less."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:171
msgid "Efficient Factories"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:172
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Non-Barren, Non-Homeworld</mark> Colonies that "
"will produce 5 CP this Economic Phase produce 6 CP instead. <mark class"
"=\"hl-blue\">The max gain is 8 CP on normal maps. In situations where one"
" of these fully grown colonies would produce something other than 5 CP, "
"the colony produces 1 extra CP when fully grown.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:179
msgid "Omega Crystals"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:180
msgid ""
"All the player's CAs, BCs, BBs, DNs, and Titans are equipped with the "
"Omega Crystal. If a ship with the Omega Crystal is present in battle the "
"player may activate it after a Group has fired (enemy or friendly). That "
"Group must reroll ALL of its dice. The first set of results from that "
"Group is undone and replaced by the new rolls. The new results must be "
"accepted, even if worse for the Omega Crystal player. No matter how many "
"ships with the Omega Crystal are present, the player may only ever do "
"this once during the entire battle. If the ships retreat and then "
"subsequently engage in battle, they may again use the Omega Crystal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:182 app/data/cards.py:206 app/data/cards.py:222
#: app/data/cards.py:230 app/data/cards.py:1616 app/data/cards.py:1674
#: app/data/cards.py:2109
msgid "When first used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:187
msgid "Cryogenic Stasis Pods"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:188
msgid "Boarding Ships & Transports pay 1/2 maintenance."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:195
msgid "Minesweep Jammer"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:196
msgid ""
"Minesweepers used against you are treated as having one level less of "
"Minesweeping technology. So Minesweepers with only level 1 would not "
"sweep any Mines at all."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:198
msgid "At the start of combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:203
msgid "Air Support"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:204
msgid ""
"Transports function in ground combat as B6-2-x2 units. (They must survive"
" the space combat to be used this way.) Only the modifiers for Ground "
"Units are applied to Transports being used as <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Air Support</span>. Any damage that they took during the "
"space battle is considered repaired before the start of the ground "
"combat. They may be fired at by opposing Ground Units. They may not be "
"removed to garrison the planet. If no other Ground Units are available to"
" be removed to garrison the planet, the planet is not captured."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:211
msgid "Hidden Turret"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:212
msgid "Minesweepers fire as E3 units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:214
msgid "When a SW is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:219
msgid "Stealth Field Emitter"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:220
msgid "Your ships go back to their unrevealed side after combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:227
msgid "Advanced Comm Array"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:228
msgid ""
"If a ship otherwise qualifies for the Reaction Move ability, they may "
"react into an adjacent, non-battle hex when an opponent moves into that "
"hex. This stops the other player's movement. During combat, the reacting "
"player is considered the attacker in that battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:235
msgid "Mobile Analysis Bay"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:236
msgid ""
"You can gain technology from captured ships in any Economic Phase after "
"they are captured without having to scrap them. They do not have to be at"
" a Shipyard. May only be used one time on each captured ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:243
msgid "Adaptive Cloaking Device"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:244
msgid ""
"If your enemy does not have Scanners equal to or greater than your "
"Cloaking, your Raiders fire with a +2 to their Attack Strength (instead "
"of the usual +1) in the 1st Round. If they do have Scanners equal to your"
" Cloaking then your Cloak is nullified, but in the 1st Round they fire as"
" A-Class, 2nd Round as B-Class, 3rd Round as C-Class, 4th & later as "
"D-Class. This card only impacts Raiders, even if you also have the <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Cloaking Geniuses #50</span> Empire Advantage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:246
msgid "When a Raider is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:251
msgid "Fearless Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:252
msgid ""
"The ethos of this race places a high value on proving their courage. All "
"of their combat-capable ships and Shipyards (excluding Boarding Ships and"
" Ground Units) fire as A-Class ships in the first round of combat (only)."
" <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Their Missiles hit as C-Class in the first "
"round.</mark> After the first round everything reverts to its normal "
"Class. However, none of their ships are able to retreat from combat until"
" after Round 3 (this may be modified by e.g. Crew Cards). Their ships "
"would still fire as E-Class (or F-Class for Boarding Ships) when in "
"Asteroids or Nebulae (5.8)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:254 app/data/cards.py:262 app/data/cards.py:278
#: app/data/cards.py:310 app/data/cards.py:353
msgid "When first entering any combat, including Aliens."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:259
msgid "Warrior Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:260
msgid ""
"+1 to Attack Strength for all non-Boarding Ship units when they are the "
"attacker in a battle. –1 to the Attack Strength for all non-Boarding Ship"
" units when they are the defender in a battle. No advantage is given when"
" bombarding a planet or to ground troops."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:267
msgid "Celestial Knights"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:268
msgid ""
"Once per space battle (not ground combat or Colony bombardment), after "
"the first round, at the start of a round, this race may declare a "
"\"charge\". All of their units (including Boarding Ships <mark class"
"=\"hl-blue\">and Missile Boats</mark> but not any kind of Bases, <mark "
"class=\"hl-blue\">DSN, <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Ion Cannons "
"#134</span></mark> and Shipyards) get two attacks <mark class=\"hl-"
"blue\">(or fire two missiles)</mark> in that round only. However, in all "
"following rounds all enemy units get +1 to their Attack Strength <mark "
"class=\"hl-blue\">(this does not apply to fire against Missiles, but does"
" apply against any kind of Bases, DSN, and Shipyards)</mark>. In "
"addition, the charging ships may not retreat the round after the charge."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:270
msgid "When a \"charge\" is declared for the first time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:275
msgid "Giant Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:276
msgid ""
"The Hull Size of all units (except Ground Units and Missiles) of this "
"race is increased by one. This impacts everything that has to do with "
"Hull Size – SYs needed to construct (including for Miners, Colony Ships, "
"and MS Pipelines), damage to destroy, technology that can be carried, "
"maintenance, boarding parties, etc. The cost to build the ships remains "
"the same. Captured ships of this race retain their Hull Size. <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Giant Race</span> may not research Fighters and may "
"not get them by any other means (capturing technology, etc.). Decoys "
"continue to have a Hull Size of zero and do not need a SY to build. <mark"
" class=\"hl-blue\">Missiles still only take 1 hit to destroy.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:283
msgid "Industrious Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:284
msgid ""
"When this race researches Terraforming 1, they may colonize Asteroids "
"exactly as if they were a Barren Planet. The Asteroids still retain their"
" normal terrain effects. Titans may not destroy an Asteroid like it would"
" a planet and may not attack Asteroid Colonies at all. Other players may "
"not attack an Asteroid Colony with Ground Units. If playing with the "
"Short Game Victory Condition (Colony Points; CSB 1.1.7), Asteroid "
"Colonies in Deep Space do not count as a Colony Point. If colonizing an "
"Asteroid, the player does NOT get an Alien Technology Card (11.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:286
msgid "When an asteroid is colonized for the first time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:291
msgid "Ancient Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:292
msgid ""
"At the start of the game (before it begins), this player reveals that "
"they are the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Ancient Race</span>, then "
"explores all hexes adjacent to their Homeworld. They then explore six of "
"the hexes that are adjacent to those hexes (these will be two hexes from "
"their Homeworld). This means that it is possible for some of the hexes "
"that are two spaces away from their Homeworld to not be explored "
"(depending on the setup). They immediately collect up to 3 Minerals that "
"were revealed and place those Minerals on their Homeworld. Next, this "
"player places up to 3 Colony Ships from their supply (Colony Ship side "
"up) on any non-barren planets that are revealed in this way (3 Colony "
"Ships still start at the Homeworld). They will become Colony 1s at the "
"end of the first Economic Phase. This represents colonists that have made"
" contact with this player's race again after spending hundreds of years "
"in cryogenic sleep while in transit to these planets. Now that the "
"\"modern\" faster than light drive has been perfected, the Colonies will "
"grow and become part of the Empire."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:294
msgid "At the start of the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:299
msgid "Space Pilgrims"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:300
msgid ""
"This race has a greater understanding of space and is at home in it. They"
" suffer no movement penalties in Nebulae or Asteroids. Their ships never "
"get sucked into Black Holes and they are never Lost in Space. They may "
"even use the Black Hole Slingshot optional rule automatically, without "
"having to roll for destruction. They still are destroyed by Danger! "
"markers and other terrain still affects them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:302
msgid ""
"When entering a Black Hole or Lost in Space marker or if they ignore the "
"movement penalty of an Asteroid or Nebula. In order to keep their "
"advantage secret, they may choose to roll when entering a Black Hole hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:307
msgid "Hive Mind"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:308
msgid ""
"This race learns and adapts in each battle. Starting in round 2 of a "
"battle, all of this race's units get +1 to their Defense Strength. "
"Starting in round 4, all units also get +1 to their Attack Strength. "
"Starting in round 6, all units get +1 to their Hull Size. These same "
"modifiers also apply to ground combat, but the ground combat is "
"considered to have started with round 1 even if a space battle preceded "
"it. If the attacker does not get to fire in the first round of ground "
"combat (because of not having Drop Ships), that still counts as the first"
" round of combat. They do not get these benefits while bombarding "
"planets. <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Missiles receive the attack and defense "
"strength benefits, but not the hull size benefit.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:315
msgid "Nano-technology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:316
msgid ""
"This race's units may instantly upgrade to the newest technology for free"
" regardless of location. If they do so they must not move that turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:323
msgid "Quick Learners"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:324
msgid ""
"These start with Military Academy level 1 and roll 2 dice (taking the "
"best result) when checking to see if a ship increases in Experience. "
"Other Empires may NEVER gain Military Academy technology from this race."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:326
msgid "When rolling to see if a ship gains Experience."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:331
msgid "Gifted Scientists"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:332
#, python-format
msgid ""
"This highly technological race gets a 33% discount (rounded up and "
"applied before any other discounts) when researching any technology. "
"However, every unit they build (Colony Ship, Decoy, Scout, Pipeline, "
"etc.) costs 1 CP more."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:339
msgid "Master Engineers"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:341
msgid ""
"This race uses a highly advanced, but unstable form of faster-than-light "
"drive. <mark class=\"hl-blue\">This empire starts the game with Move 2 "
"and Fast 1 technologies. In addition, each full-strength colony can "
"produce and retrofit ships as if it had 1 SY present. This may be "
"combined with actual SY that are built.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:342
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Full Strength Colony without an SY and with SY Tech 3 could"
" produce a BC.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:345
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">At the end of the game.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:350
msgid "Insectoids"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:351
msgid ""
"This race reproduces and builds very rapidly. The Hull Size of all units "
"(except Ground Units and Missiles) of this race is decreased by one. "
"Except as noted, this impacts everything that has to do with Hull Size – "
"SYs needed to construct (including for Miners, Colony Ships, and MS "
"pipelines), damage to destroy, tech that can be carried, maintenance, "
"boarding parties, etc. The cost to build the ships remains the same. A "
"ship such as a DD, which has a Hull Size of 0, would pay no maintenance, "
"not be allowed to carry any attack or defense tech, and could upgrade "
"technology at a SY for no CP cost. A ship with a Hull Size of 0 would "
"still be destroyed by 1 hit and would be considered to have a Hull Size "
"of 1 for the purpose of any Experience roll. Ships with a Hull Size of 0 "
"are considered to have a Hull Size of 1/2 for the purpose of using "
"Shipyard capacity. For example: 1 Shipyard at Shipyard Tech 2 could build"
" 3 DDs in an Economic Phase. <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Insectoids</span> may not research Military Academies or "
"Fighters and may not get them by any means (capturing technology, etc.). "
"Captured ships of this race retain their Hull Size. <mark class=\"hl-"
"blue\">Insectoid Starbases may still mount Attack 4.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:358
msgid "Immortals"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:359
msgid ""
"This race reproduces very slowly, but never dies of old age. They have "
"developed extra shielding and a system of reserve power in an attempt to "
"preserve the lives of their people. One time in each round of combat, "
"this race may choose to ignore one point of damage. This means that it is"
" impossible for one of their ships to be destroyed in a one-on-one battle"
" <mark class=\"hl-blue\">(unless the other ship is a Titan or Missile "
"Boat or uses Resource Cards). An Alternate Empire player cannot ignore a "
"hit against one of their Missiles.</mark> However, because a large seed "
"population is needed for their Colonies, each Colony Ship costs 2 CP "
"more. They may not choose to ignore a boarding hit. Captured ships retain"
" this ability. However, only a hit on the captured ship(s) can be "
"ignored. <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Immortals</span> may not research"
" Boarding and may not get it by any means (capturing technology, etc.). "
"If playing with any rule that normally would allow a player to carry CP "
"over into the start of the game <mark class=\"hl-blue\">(like the <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Technology Head Start #148</span> Scenario "
"Modifier)</mark>, the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Immortals</span> may"
" not and will lose any CP not spent on research. <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Immortals</span> cannot use their special ability against "
"Bombardment Damage or during Ground Combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:361
msgid "When they first choose to ignore 1 hit in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:366
msgid "Expert Tacticians"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:367
msgid ""
"This race of superior tacticians gets the +1 Attack Fleet Size Bonus as "
"soon as they have one more combat-capable ship in a battle than their "
"opponent (they don't need to have a 2:1 advantage). In addition, "
"opponents do not get the Fleet Size Bonus against them unless they "
"outnumber them by 3:1. If the opposing fleet has <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Agent Smith #200</span> or has an <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Admiral Of The Navy #245 #246</span> (or any combination "
"thereof), everything cancels each other out and the Fleet Size Bonus is "
"given at 2:1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:369
msgid "When they first choose to use their improved Fleet Size Bonuses in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:374
msgid "Horsemen of the Plains"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:375
msgid ""
"This race developed from a culture that valued the ability to strike "
"quickly and evade. If a ship of this race could otherwise retreat, it may"
" do so at the end of a round of combat, even if it fired during that "
"round. It does not need to wait for its turn to fire to retreat. They "
"could retreat as early as the end of Round 1, before Round 2 begins. In "
"addition, all of this player's ships always get +2 to their Attack "
"Strength when firing on a planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:377
msgid "When they first use one of their abilities."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:382
msgid "And We Still Carry Swords"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:383
msgid ""
"This race loves physical combat. This race starts with Ground Combat 2. "
"All of their boarding attacks get +1 to their Attack Strength and all "
"boarding attacks against them get -1 to their Attack Strength. In "
"addition, all of their Ground Units, including Militia, get +1 to their "
"Attack and Defense Strength (whether attacking or defending). Other "
"Empires may NEVER gain Ground Combat tech from this race."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:385
msgid "When engaging in boarding attack or ground invasion for the first time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:390 app/data/cards.py:824
msgid "Amazing Diplomats"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:391
msgid ""
"Non-Player Aliens do not attack this race and this race may both move "
"through their System and stack with them. NPAs with the <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Aggressive #p1</span> trait do not attack them. While"
" the alien ships will not leave the System, they will defend against "
"attacks from other players. This player may colonize alien planets as if "
"the aliens were not there (and gain an Alien Technology card). This "
"represents them developing a relationship, trade, and an outpost on that "
"planet. A Colony on an alien planet is treated like a player's Colony in "
"every respect. If the alien ships are subsequently destroyed by another "
"player, the Colony still continues until destroyed normally."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:393
msgid ""
"When entering a NPA hex for the first time or if <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Aggressive #p1</span> NPA would attack them."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:398
msgid "Traders"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:399
msgid "Gets one extra CP for each colony connected by an MS Pipeline."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:406
msgid "Cloaking Geniuses"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:407
msgid ""
"After researching Cloaking 1, all of their Scouts and Destroyers also get"
" the benefit of Cloaking. After researching Cloaking level 2, all of "
"their Cruisers also get the benefit of Cloaking. If not nullified by "
"scanners the SCs, DDs & CAs do get the +1 to their Attack Strength during"
" the first firing round. If nullified by Scanners, these ships fire where"
" they normally would according to their Weapon Class rating (a CA would "
"fire as C-Class). This is not an instant upgrade. Any ships already "
"produced would have to be refitted. A note will need to be made on "
"existing Groups in the margin of the Ship Technology Sheet. Captured "
"ships of this race retain their Cloaking ability (and can be upgraded)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:409
msgid ""
"When a cloaked SC/DD/CA is encountered in combat or moves through an "
"enemy ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:414
msgid "Star Wolves"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:415
msgid ""
"Each of this race's SCs, DDs, and Fighters get +1 to their Attack "
"Strength when firing on a unit with a Hull Size of 2 or greater. In "
"addition, their DDs cost 1 less <mark class=\"hl-blue\">(8 CP for Base "
"Empires, or 9 CP for Alternate Empires).</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:417
msgid "When they first use their ability."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:422
msgid "Power to the People"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:423
msgid ""
"Mines, Colony Ships, Miners, and MS Pipelines are automatically and "
"instantly upgraded to the player's current Movement technology (they will"
" be able to move more than 1 space per turn)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:425
msgid ""
"When a Miner, CO, MS Pipeline, or revealed Mine moves faster than normal "
"for the first time."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:430
msgid "House of Speed"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:432
msgid ""
"This race starts with Movement 7 tech, but their ships sacrifice "
"defensive abilities. Opponents (including NPAs, Doomsday Machines, Space "
"Amoebas, and Space Pirates) get a +2 to their Attack Strength (even when "
"boarding) when firing at ships of this race (including Fighters, but not "
"any type of Bases, SYs, DSN, Colonies, Space Stations, or Ground Units)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:433
msgid ""
"Also, their Movement technology gives off such a strong energy signature "
"that they may never research Cloaking or get it by any other means "
"(capturing technology, etc.). They may use captured Raiders but may not "
"increase the speed of the captured Raider. Captured ships of this race "
"retain both their speed advantage and their defensive liability. However,"
" their movement technology is so complex that other Empires may NEVER "
"gain Movement technology from this race (either by scrapping boarded "
"ships or capturing planets)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:436
msgid ""
"The first time a ship moves more than 1 hex in a turn or the first time "
"its ships are in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:441
msgid "Powerful Psychics"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:442
msgid ""
"This race starts with Exploration 1 technology. In addition, their "
"sensors are more advanced. This player may reveal all face down Groups "
"that are adjacent to one of their ships with Exploration technology (e.g."
" CAs, Flagship, Unique ships). These counters are left face up (as if "
"they had been encountered in combat). However, the technology on the "
"revealed ships is not revealed by this power. Since their Exploration "
"technology is partially based on their psychic powers, other Empires may "
"NEVER gain Exploration technology from this race (either by scrapping "
"boarded ships or capturing planets)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:444
msgid "The first time a stack is inspected."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:449
msgid "Shape Shifters"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:451
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">This Empire may place Decoys in any hex with a "
"friendly combat ship in addition to any hex with a Colony. Each Economic "
"Phase they get two free Decoy units. If they run out of Decoys, they may "
"use any spare counter as a Decoy if they mark it as such on their Ship "
"Tech sheet.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:452
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: CA <mark class=\"hl-green\">group</mark> 2 can be marked as a"
" Decoy on the Ship Tech Sheet and used as a Decoy.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:453
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">In combat, they do not have to reveal any "
"technology possessed unless it actually would change the result of a "
"combat roll, in which case they announce it after the roll.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:454
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A CA Group has Attack 2 Tech. This is not revealed. After "
"rolling an Attack, one of the dice misses by one. The player then must "
"reveal that he has Attack 2 and it scores a hit.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:455
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Once per game, they may retreat their ships as if"
" they had just played Resource Card <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Retreat When Engaged #107</span>.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:458
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">When a non-Decoy effect of this card is "
"used.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:463
msgid "On Board Workshop"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:464
msgid ""
"Each CV, BV, and Titan may be used to build one Fighter during the "
"Economic Phase as long as there is room to store the Fighter built. This "
"includes Fighter technology that has just been researched. The Fighter "
"costs the same as if it was produced at a Shipyard. No other ships that "
"carry Fighters (like Unique ships) can do this except <mark class=\"hl-"
"blue\">Alternate Empire BBs and DNs</mark>. During a Movement Turn, one "
"Fighter may be refitted and the ship carrying it may move as long as the "
"FTR accompanies it for the entire movement phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:466
msgid "When a CV/BV/Titan is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:471
msgid "Superhighway"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:472
msgid ""
"Each ship that spends its entire move on an MS Pipeline chain may move "
"two extra hexes instead of one."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:473
msgid ""
"The flavor text on the card comes from an old German slogan against speed"
" limits on the autobahn—roughly, \"Free roads for free citizens\"."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:475
msgid "The first time it is used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:480
msgid "On the Move"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:481
msgid ""
"Shipyards and all types of Bases have Move 1 and may attack and explore. "
"They may not retreat from combat, and they can never be upgraded to a "
"higher Movement technology. They may move an extra hex if using MS "
"Pipelines or Black Hole Slingshot. Shipyards may only build ships during "
"the Economic Phase if they are in the same hex with a friendly Colony "
"that produced CP during this Economic Phase. However, they may be used to"
" upgrade ships normally no matter where they are on the map. Both the SY "
"and group being upgraded may not move when performing the retrofit. All "
"other rules for Shipyards and Bases are the same."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:483
msgid ""
"The first time a revealed Shipyard/Base moves, the first time a Shipyard "
"or a (non advanced) Base is revealed while not at a Colony, or the first "
"time a Shipyard/Base is in battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:488
msgid "Longbowmen"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:489
msgid ""
"This race uses long range torpedoes. The Weapon Class of their <mark "
"class=\"hl-blue\">SC, DD, CA, BC, Flagship, Missiles, and nullified "
"Raiders</mark> is increased by one letter (C-Class becomes B-Class, "
"B-Class becomes A-Class, etc.). A-Class ships remain A-Class and get no "
"benefit. <mark class=\"hl-blue\">This benefit is only if the battle is in"
" open space, Space Stations, planets, Minerals, or Space Wrecks.</mark> "
"DDs with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Long Lance Torpedoes #5</span> "
"and Fighters stay at B-Class and get no benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:491
msgid ""
"When first entering combat, including Aliens, with one of the affected "
"ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:496
msgid "Fast Replicators"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:497
msgid ""
"Replicators start with Move 2 tech. Future levels of Movement technology "
"only cost 15 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:504
msgid "Green Replicators"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:505
msgid "Replicator Colonies do not begin to deplete until Econ Phase 13."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:507
msgid "At the start of Economic Phase 10."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:512
msgid "Improved Gunnery"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:513
msgid ""
"The Replicator Flagship and all Type XIII and Type XV ships are equipped "
"with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Second Salvo</span>. When they start "
"a turn with 4 RP, all of their ships have their Tactics level increased "
"by 1 and type V ships gain +1 Attack."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:515
msgid ""
"When entering combat, including Aliens, with a Type V, XIII, XV or the "
"Flagship, or when a ship reveals a higher Tactics level for any reason."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:520
msgid "Warp Gates"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:521
msgid ""
"Replicator Explore Ships and the Flagship are equipped with <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Warp Gates</span>. Explore ships still have a Hull "
"Size of 2, but only take one hull to produce (and only count as one hull "
"if converted to a different ship)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:523
msgid ""
"The first time a Warp Gate is used, or a ship equipped with one is in "
"combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:528
msgid "Advanced Research"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:529
msgid "Replicators begin the game with one extra RP. Buying RP costs only 25."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:536
msgid "Replicator Capitol"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:537
msgid ""
"The Replicator Homeworld may produce an additional Hull every odd "
"Economic Phase (in addition to any other increases e.g. from spending "
"CP). The Replicators also start with 10 extra CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:544
msgid "Red Squadron"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:548
msgid ""
"Play before the battle begins, but after ships are revealed. One FTR "
"Group currently in battle gets an additional +1 to attack for the "
"remainder of the battle."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:555
msgid "Sensor Blind Spot"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:559
msgid ""
"Play before the battle begins, but after ships are revealed. A single "
"unit with a cloak that has been nullified by Scanners during combat may "
"hide in the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">sensor blind spot</span> of a "
"unit with Hull Size x3 or greater. The Raider immediately makes a retreat"
" from battle. This doesn't need to be a hex closer to a friendly Colony "
"than the hex the battle was in."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:566
msgid "Self Destruct"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:570
msgid ""
"Play after one of your ships is captured. Immediately destroy it. The "
"enemy gains no knowledge of your abilities from capturing this ship. The "
"ship still counts as captured for the purpose of Ship Experience "
"Promotion Rolls (37.3.2)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:577
msgid "Concealed Minefield"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:581
msgid ""
"Play before the battle begins, but after ships are revealed. Before Enemy"
" Minesweepers sweep your Mines, one of your Mines may detonate as normal "
"– even against a Minesweeper (17.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:588 app/data/cards.py:603 app/data/cards.py:618
#: app/data/cards.py:633
msgid "Heroic Ships"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:593 app/data/cards.py:608 app/data/cards.py:623
#: app/data/cards.py:638
msgid ""
"Play before the battle begins, but after ships are revealed. Select one "
"of the ships listed on the card title (a single ship, not a Group). It is"
" <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Heroic</span> for the rest of the game. "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Heroic</span> ships get +1 to their Attack"
" and Defense. They also take one more hit to destroy (this is cumulative "
"with the <i>Legendary</i> bonus; 37.0). They do not pay maintenance. "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Heroic</span> status is lost if the ship "
"is captured or destroyed. Instead of using a number counter under the "
"ship, use one of the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Heroic</span> "
"counters with a star on it. If the ship ever gets flipped face down "
"again, it will look like any other ship. In the very rare case where a "
"player may have 2 <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Heroic</span> ships of "
"the same type in the same hex, they may flip the <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Heroic</span> counter to the 2-star side."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:594 app/data/cards.py:609 app/data/cards.py:624
#: app/data/cards.py:639
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-blue\">When playing with Crew Cards (12.0), these "
"Resource Cards cannot be used to make ships <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Heroic</span>. Instead, they can be played at any time to "
"draw 2 Crew Cards and keep 1. They may be immediately assigned or "
"assigned during the next Econ Phase.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:596
msgid ""
"<i>\"There will always be a Rodger Young in the Federation fleet.\"</i> "
"Inspired by Admiral Ernest J. King who stated that <i>\"There’ll always "
"be an England in the United States Navy.\"</i> This was in response to "
"DE-635 USS England’s sinking six Japanese Submarines between 18-27 May "
"1944."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:597 app/data/cards.py:612 app/data/cards.py:627
#: app/data/cards.py:641 app/data/cards.py:653 app/data/cards.py:664
msgid ""
"Play this card to build an extra Hull on the Replicator Homeworld. Only "
"one of these cards may be played at the start of an  economic Phase. This"
" card may be combined with buying an extra Hull and with the <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Replicator Capitol #65</span> Empire Advantage so "
"that up to 4 Hulls could theoretically be produced in one Economic Phase."
" Since it only takes three ships of Hull Size 1 to build a Type XIII or "
"Type XV, in this extreme case the Replicator could theoretically build a "
"Type XIII or XV AND another Hull Size 1 ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:611
msgid ""
"<i>\"All Hands to General Quarters! ECM to Maximum! Hard a Port! Prepare "
"to engage a major portion of the enemy fleet.\"</i> Inspired by the "
"orders given by Commander Evans aboard DD-557 USS Johnston at the Battle "
"of Leyte Gulf."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:626
msgid ""
"<i>\"The Empire expects every member of this crew to do his duty "
"today!\"</i> Inspired by Admiral Nelson’s speech before the Battle of "
"Trafalgar."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:647 app/data/cards.py:659
msgid "Heroic Ground Unit"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:651 app/data/cards.py:663
msgid ""
"Play before the first round of a ground battle begins. Select one of your"
" non-Militia Ground Units (one unit, not an entire Group). It will be "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Heroic</span> for the rest of the game or "
"until it is destroyed. <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Heroic</span> "
"Ground Units get +1 to their Attack/Defense/Hull Size. This card may not "
"be combined with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Defending Familiar "
"Terrain #76 #170</span> to create a <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Heroic</span> Heavy Infantry Militia."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:652
msgid ""
"\"<i>\"For the Honor of the Regiment!\"</i> The art used for this card is"
" the crest of the regiment that Oliver Upshaw, this game’s developer, "
"served in."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:670 app/data/cards.py:1516
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Defending Familiar Terrain</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:674 app/data/cards.py:1520
msgid ""
"Play before the first round of a ground battle to upgrade a planet's "
"Militia to Heavy Infantry for the duration of the combat (21.10). May "
"even be played if the defender is only at Ground Combat 1. May be played "
"when another player attacks NPAs. A counter is provided so that the "
"players can keep separate any real defending Infantry/Heavy Infantry."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:675 app/data/cards.py:686 app/data/cards.py:697
#: app/data/cards.py:708 app/data/cards.py:719 app/data/cards.py:730
#: app/data/cards.py:1521
msgid ""
"Extra Move. Play this card before moving to move one Replicator ship (not"
" a Group), one extra space this turn. Additionally, for each other "
"Resource Card you discard unused from your hand, one additional "
"Replicator ship that is part of the same Group can also move one extra "
"space. Two of these cards cannot be used in combination to make one "
"Replicator ship move two extra spaces in one move."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:681
msgid "Research Breakthrough"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:685
msgid ""
"Play this card to allow you to research two levels of the same technology"
" in the same Economic Phase at the combined cost of the technologies in "
"question plus 5 CP. If you are using IC/RC rules (36.0), the extra cost "
"is 5 RP. This is the only card effect that cannot be canceled when "
"played. When you discard it, you do not have to announce if it was played"
" for its effect or for CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:692
msgid "Quick Study"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:696
msgid ""
"Play before a friendly or enemy Group rolls for Experience. Shift the "
"dice result by +/–2. This affects all Experience die rolls made by that "
"Group this round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:703
msgid "Discover Member of Ancient Race"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:707
msgid ""
"Play at the start of an Econ Phase where you will roll on the Space Wreck"
" Technology Table. After you roll, you may add or subtract up to 2 to the"
" dice, even looping through the results. For example, a 10 can be shifted"
" to a 2 and a 2 can be shifted to a 10."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:714
msgid "Overload Weapons"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:718
msgid ""
"For this effect, an additional Resource card must be discarded unused "
"from your hand. Play before one of your ships (not Group) fires. When "
"calculating the number needed to get a hit, double the Attack tech that "
"is on the ship. <i>For example, a BC with Attack 1 would have an Attack "
"Strength of 7</i>. If a hit is scored the target takes an extra 2 points "
"of damage. This means a SC could one shot kill a DN/BB/Base with this "
"card. <mark class=\"hl-blue\">If used on a Missile Boat, the card must be"
" played when placing the Missile, doubles the Missiles attack tech, and "
"the Missile would do 4 damage if it hits.</mark> For the rest of the "
"battle the selected ship's Attack Strength is considered to be zero. The "
"Ship Selected must mount at least Attack 1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:725
msgid "Unconventional Boarding"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:729
msgid ""
"For this effect, an additional Resource card must be discarded unused "
"from your hand. Play this card instead of performing your ship's normal "
"attacks. Select an enemy ship and attack it with a boarding strength of "
"5. Subtract the Hull Size of the targeted ship from this Attack Strength."
" Security Forces have no effect on this die roll. <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">And We Still Carry Swords #47</span> gives the +1/–1 bonus as"
" normal. Experience, except for the extra Hull of a "
"<i>Legendary</i>/<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Heroic Ship #70 #71 #72 "
"#73</span>, has no effect on this roll. Add 2 to this Attack Strength if "
"you have researched Boarding 1. Add 2 more if you have researched "
"Boarding 2. This can only be used against ships that normally can be "
"boarded. If you are not playing with Boarding Ships (19.0), then this "
"card cannot be played for its effect. <mark class=\"hl-blue\">This effect"
" can't be used against Replicators and cannot be used by or against "
"Alternate Empires or <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Immortals "
"#44</span>.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:736
msgid "Xeno-Archeology"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:740
msgid ""
"If you spend 10 CP in the next Econ Phase, you may keep the second Alien "
"Tech card that you drew when capturing a planet (11.1). This card must be"
" played before discarding one of the Alien Tech cards. If played, the 10 "
"CP must be spent in the next Econ Phase. If playing without non-player "
"Aliens, the player must normally spend 10 CP to keep one Alien Technology"
" Card. <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Xeno-Archeology</span> could be "
"played to allow the player to spend an additional 10 CP to keep the other"
" card. If this card is canceled the 10 CP does not have to be paid."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:741
msgid ""
"After having earned an Alien Technology Card, gain an RP instead of 10 "
"CP. Replicator player plays this immediately upon earning an Alien Tech "
"Card. If this card is canceled, the Replicator player still gets to turn "
"in the Alien Tech Card for 10 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:747
msgid "Missed Rendezvous"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:751
msgid ""
"Play before ships are revealed in battle. If the other side has units "
"participating in this battle that entered the hex from at least two "
"different hex sides or via Reaction Movement (35.0), all ships entering "
"through a selected hexside do not show up until the second round of "
"combat. These ships cannot retreat until the third round. For the delayed"
" units, the second round is treated as the first round, the third round "
"as the second, etc. in all respects (including when using the Empire "
"Advantages <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Fearless Race #31</span>, <span"
" class=\"text-uppercase\">Hive Mind #38</span>, etc.) Minesweepers that "
"arrive on the second round of combat cannot sweep any remaining Mines. "
"Ships with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Shield Projectors</span> that "
"arrive on the second round of combat can only protect ships that also "
"arrived in the second round of combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:758
msgid "Activate Space Monstrosity"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:762
msgid ""
"Play before Doomsday Machines (29.0) move or Space Amoebas spread (SSB "
"3.0 and CSB 10.0). Choose a Doomsday Machine or Space Amoeba. You "
"determine where it moves/spreads to, not the normal rules of the game. "
"Though you cannot select a Black Hole hex for a Space Amoeba to spread to"
" and you cannot move the DM/SA into a player's Home System hexes. The DM "
"can still only move up to two hexes and the SA will still only spread to "
"one hex. If not playing with either Doomsday Machines or Space Amoebas, "
"this card can't be used for its event."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:769
msgid "Spawn Doomsday Machine"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:773
msgid ""
"For this effect, an additional Resource card must be discarded unused "
"from your hand. This card must be played at the start of your turn prior "
"to your movement. Place a Doomsday Machine (29.0) in a Deep Space hex "
"that is adjacent to one of your SC/SCXs and does not contain any terrain "
"or unit counters. This does not cause an unrevealed SC/SCX to become "
"revealed. It is not under any player's control and will operate according"
" to the rules in section 29.0. If not playing with DMs, the card cannot "
"be played for its effect. If this card is played successfully for its "
"effect, it does not go into your discard pile; it is set aside and is "
"unusable for the rest of the game. For this card Replicator Type 0, II, "
"and IV ships are considered a SC/SCX."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:780
msgid "Spy on Board"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:784
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn or the start of an Econ Phase to flip over"
" all the enemy units or NPA Aliens in one hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:791
msgid "Provide Cover"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:795
msgid ""
"Play after an enemy Group targets one of your Groups. Designate another "
"one of your Groups as the target of the attack. The target you choose may"
" not be a Titan, any Base, <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Defense Satellite "
"Network, Ion Cannon</mark>, Shipyard, or CV/BV (if you have Fighters "
"present), or be protected by Shield Projector. It must be a legal target."
" All ships in the enemy Group must fire at the designated Group for this "
"round of battle. They gain +1 to their attack. If your Group is destroyed"
" before the last enemy ship in the Group has fired the remaining ships "
"can pick new targets and do not get the +1. If the Group selected has not"
" fired yet and it survives it must fire at the enemy Group that it "
"blocked for this round. It will also gain a +1. It it destroys the enemy "
"Group, it can switch remaining shots to new targets but doesn't get the "
"+1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:802
msgid "Alien Reinforcements"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:806
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn, the start of an Economic Phase or the "
"start of combat before ships are revealed. Select one un-colonized Deep "
"Space planet that has at least one NPA ship and randomly add 3 NPA ships "
"to it (18.0). If you are not playing with NPAs then this card cannot be "
"played for its effect. If the Replicators are in combat with the NPAs, "
"these added ships may make it possible for them to mark off having "
"encountered a Fleet Size of 5 or greater on their Production Sheet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:813
msgid "Deep Cover Operative"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:817
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn or the start of an Economic Phase. Choose "
"an opponent. You may look through that player's face up Resource Cards "
"(excluding Missions), pick one card, and add it to your hand. Removing a "
"card from a player's face up Resource Cards does not change any of the "
"effects that the card has already generated."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:828
msgid ""
"Play when one of your ships enters a Deep Space planet's hex for the "
"first time. The NPAs in this hex will treat you as if your Empire "
"Advantage is <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Amazing Diplomats #48</span> "
"for the rest of the game. If your Empire Advantage Card is <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Amazing Diplomats #48</span>, then the first time one"
" of your ships goes to that hex place a Colony 5 marker on the planet. "
"Once a player has used either version of <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Amazing Diplomats #48 #93</span> to affect a planet, no other"
" player may use either effect on that planet for the rest of the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:835
msgid "Forced System Shutdown"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:839
msgid ""
"Play during combat, after fleets are revealed but before the first round "
"starts. Select one enemy unit. For the first three battle rounds, treat "
"this unit as not having any Attack, Defense, and Tactics upgrades. If the"
" enemy does not have a spare Group counter, then they have the choice of "
"either destroying the effected ship or having this card effect the entire"
" Group. If played against Replicators, the ship gets –2 to its attack "
"(min of 1) and defense (min of 0), Tactics is not affected."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:846
msgid "Smuggler's Route"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:851
msgid "Can be played in one of two ways:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:852
msgid ""
"• At the start of your player turn or the start of an Economic Phase "
"select any unrevealed System marker. Remove the marker from the board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:853
msgid ""
"• At the start of your player turn, select one Nebula, Asteroid hex, or "
"Black Hole. All your ships that start their movement beside this hex this"
" turn may move through it (provided they have enough movement) without "
"having to stop or having to roll a Black Hole survival check (6.3). This "
"card cannot be combined with a Black Hole Slingshot Maneuver (31.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:861
msgid "Planetary Bombardment"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:865
msgid ""
"Play before bombardment of a Colony starts (5.10). If played by the "
"defender, give +2 to all of the attacker's die rolls. If played by the "
"attacker, give -2 to all their die rolls. Titans are not affected by this"
" card. Transports using Anti-Replicator technology against a Start-level "
"Replicator Colony are not affected by this card (40.2.5)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:872
msgid "Update Your Charts"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:877
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn or the start of an Econ Phase. Can be "
"played in one of two ways:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:878
msgid ""
"• Select a hex that is beside an unrevealed Deep Space marker and that "
"does not contain a System marker or a player unit. Add a random Deep "
"Space marker that was set aside at the beginning of the game to that hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:879
msgid ""
"• Select two unrevealed Deep Space markers and exchange their positions "
"on the board."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:887
msgid "Play Dead"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:891
msgid ""
"To play this card, an additional Resource card must be discarded unused "
"from your hand. Play after one of your non-Titan ships is destroyed. "
"Treat this ship as screened for the rest of the battle. It cannot be "
"targeted for the rest of the battle. It cannot fire nor can it retreat. "
"If you win the battle, the ship recovers all damage and rejoins your "
"other ships. If you lose the battle, the enemy will destroy it at no "
"cost. The enemy does get to roll for Experience when they \"kill\" the "
"ship during the battle (37.0). Experience gained by this roll is not lost"
" if the ship survives the battle. <mark class=\"hl-blue\">This effect "
"cannot be used to save a Missile.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:894
msgid "This effect cannot be used to save a Missile."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:900
msgid "Overconfidence"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:904
msgid ""
"Play during combat, after fleets are revealed but before the first round "
"starts. Enemy ships in this battle may not retreat (5.9) until one round "
"later than normal (Round 3 for most ships, round 4 if combined with <span"
" class=\"text-uppercase\">Missed Rendezvous #84</span>, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:911
msgid "Hidden Power"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:915 app/data/cards.py:1557
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn or the start of an Econ Phase. Immediately"
" draw up to 3 Resource Cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:922
msgid "Sanctions"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:926
msgid ""
"Play at the start of your turn. Choose one opponent, randomly select one "
"Resource Card from their hand (without looking), and place it face up in "
"their discard pile."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:933
msgid "Coup"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:938
msgid ""
"Play on a player after a battle where they lost 6+ Hull Points of combat-"
"capable units. In the next Econ Phase, their Homeworld produces half the "
"usual income (round down). The Hull Points must be lost in combat where "
"dice are rolled to take out the ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:939
msgid "• Ships lost to Doomsday Machines or Space Amoebas DO count."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:940
msgid "• Bases, Starbases, DSN, and Shipyards DO count."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:941
msgid "• Ships that are captured DO count."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:942
msgid "• Ships lost to Mines DO NOT count."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:943
msgid "• Mines DO NOT count."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:944
msgid "• Ground Units DO NOT count."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:945
msgid "• <mark class=\"hl-blue\">Missiles DO NOT count.</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:946
#, python-format
msgid ""
"For the purpose of counting Hull Points for this card, ignore all special"
" rules, Empire Advantages, and Alien Tech Cards. Count the Hull Points as"
" shown on the counter. In the case of Unique Ships (41.0), count the Hull"
" Size that was paid for. There is no negative effect when played against "
"the Replicators; instead, the player that destroyed the Hull Points has "
"their Homeworld produce 50% greater income (round down) in the next "
"Economic Phase. <i>(Representing a surge in loyalty and hope from getting"
" an important victory.)</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:954
msgid "Retreat When Engaged"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:958
msgid ""
"Play during a battle before ships are revealed. ALL of your mobile units "
"MUST retreat. This includes Decoys, Mines, Titans, Miners, Colony Ships, "
"Pipelines and your Bases/Shipyards if they can move. If you have a Colony"
" in that space, you may leave as many Fighters or Ground Units as you "
"wish at the Colony."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:965
msgid "Collateral Damage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:969
msgid ""
"Play when a combat-capable unit of either side is destroyed in space "
"combat at a planet. Drop the growth level of the Colony by one level. "
"This cannot cause the Colony to drop below the Colony marker's lowest "
"value, e.g., 0, Start, or 5 (for Homeworlds)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:976
msgid "Minerals +5/–3"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:980 app/data/cards.py:1531
msgid ""
"Play at the start of an Economic Phase. Designate one Mineral on a planet"
" or a Miner in a Nebula harvesting resources (34.0) during the Economic "
"Phase. That Mineral/Miner will be worth 5 more or 3 less than normal "
"(your choice – you can either increase your own/teammates' income or "
"decrease your opponents'). If played on Replicators, play this card when "
"the Replicator Player picks up the Mineral."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:987
msgid "Splash Damage"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:991
msgid ""
"Play when a combat-capable unit is destroyed in space combat. Deal 1 "
"damage to X other non-screened enemy combat-capable units <mark class"
"=\"hl-blue\">(including Missiles)</mark> in this space battle, where X is"
" the Hull Size of the destroyed ship. For each ship that is damaged by "
"this, roll a die. On a 6-10 they ignore the damage. Titans, Doomsday "
"Machines, Space Amoebas, CVs/BVs protected by Fighters, and Units "
"protected by Shield Projectors cannot be selected as targets of the <span"
" class=\"text-uppercase\">splash damage</span>. Ships destroyed by <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Splash Damage</span> do not generate an "
"Experience Roll (37.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:998
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Carthage</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:999
msgid ""
"The Barren Planet in each Home System is occupied by a hostile alien "
"race. It is treated like a Deep Space planet, complete with NPAs, drawing"
" Technology Cards, etc. It cannot have the <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Aggressive #p1</span> Deep Space Planet Attribute. If that "
"attribute is revealed on that planet, discard it, and immediately draw "
"another. Each player cannot explore or enter Deep Space until they defeat"
" these NPAs in their home system. <i>They are the major competing power "
"in your region and must be defeated before conquering the universe.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1005
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Fruitful</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1006
msgid ""
"Barren Planets in a Home System do not need Terraforming to colonize, but"
" are still considered Barren for the purpose of other cards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1012
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Worth the Effort</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1013
msgid ""
"If a Colony on a Barren Planet produces any CP, it produces 2 extra CP "
"(or the appropriate type of point if a Facility is present). Do not use "
"(draw another card) if Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1019
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Extinct Alien Empire</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1020
msgid ""
"The Barren Planet in each player's Home System has no NPAs but provides "
"Alien Technology Cards when colonized; Draw 4 cards and keep 2. Do not "
"use (draw another card) if Replicators are in the game. The <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Xeno-Archeology #82 #83</span> Resource Card may not "
"be used when colonizing this planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1026
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Expert Empires</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1027
msgid ""
"When drawing Empire Advantage cards, draw 4 and keep 2. <i>Warning – "
"there can be some crazy combinations when playing with this variant, but "
"it is fun.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1033
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">No Sensor Lock Possible</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1034
msgid ""
"No combat can occur in Nebulae, all other rules remain the same. It is a "
"neutral space. Both combat and non-combat ships of all players may enter "
"and end their turn in the hex, ignoring the units of other players. "
"Replicators do not gain RPs from enemy units in this hex."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1040
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Thick Asteroids</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1041
msgid ""
"All other rules for Asteroids are the same, except all ships take one "
"damage in Asteroids. Non-combat ships and ships with one Hull are "
"destroyed; all other ships have one damage on them while in the Asteroids"
" (this is an exception to the rule that only one ship in a group may have"
" damage). They are immediately healed upon exiting Asteroids. This "
"applies to the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Space Pilgrims #37</span> "
"Empire Advantage as well. Missiles cannot be fired in Asteroids. The "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Insectoids #43</span>, <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Giant Race #34</span>, and <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Industrious Race #35</span> Empire Advantages cannot be used "
"if this is in effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1047
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Advanced Navigation</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1048
msgid ""
"Ships do not have to start adjacent in order to enter Asteroids or "
"Nebulae but must still stop upon entering. All other rules are the same."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1054
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Expensive Ships</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1055
msgid ""
"All units except Ground Units cost 1 CP extra to build. For the "
"Replicator player the first 15 CP of Minerals collected provide no "
"income."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1061
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Planetary Gates</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1062
msgid ""
"All planets within 3 hexes are connected by <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Planetary Gates</span> (see CSB 9.0 but do not place extra "
"Barren Planets at setup)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1068
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">A Way Through</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1069
msgid ""
"All rules for Super Novas are the same except they can be entered by "
"specific type(s) of ship, and anything being carried by that ship "
"(Fighters, Ground Units, etc. on board). For that type of ship the Super "
"Nova is like an empty hex. During setup, roll a die: 1-2 SC, 3-4 DD, 5 "
"CA, 6 BC, 7 BB, 8 Raiders, 9 MB & CV & BV, 10 Flagship & Transport. "
"Indicate the result of the roll by placing ship(s) from an unused empire "
"on this card or writing a note on scratch paper. Do not use (draw another"
" card) if Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1075
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Better Homes</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1076
msgid ""
"Home Planets produce 10 CP more if at full strength. The Replicator "
"Homeworld produces 2 extra Hull Points if at full strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1082
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Improved Colony Ships</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1083
msgid ""
"When colonizing a planet (4.4) the colony starts at 1 CP. Bombardment and"
" other game effects can reduce colonies to 0 as normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1089
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Close Quarters</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1091
msgid "Some ships have lower Weapon classes:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1092
msgid "• DD, CA, Raiders with nullified cloak are E-Class."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1093
msgid "• BC and Fighters are D-Class."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1094
msgid "• BB are C-Class."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1095
msgid "• DN are B-Class."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1096
msgid ""
"These classes can be increased by Alien Tech Cards, Empire Advantages, "
"and other effects. Unique Ships cannot be used. Do not use (draw another "
"card) if Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1103
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Big Ships and Tractor Beams</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1104
msgid ""
"All players start with Ship Size 4. Replicators start with SC/DD/CA "
"already checked off. All players start with Tractor Beams, and all BBs "
"and Type XI Replicator Ships are automatically equipped with them. Do not"
" draw a Special Ability for BBs if using an Alternate Empire; they get "
"this instead. The cost to research Ship Size 7 is 50 CP instead of 30 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1110
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Big Ships and Shield Projectors</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1111
msgid ""
"All players start with Ship Size 5. Replicators start with SC/DD/CA/BC "
"already checked off. All players start with Shield Projectors and all DNs"
" and Type XIIIs Replicator Ships are automatically equipped with them. Do"
" not draw a Special Ability for DNs in an Alternate Empire; they get this"
" instead. The cost to research Ship Size 7 is 60 instead of 30. If the "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Big Ships and Tractor Beams #125</span> "
"card is also drawn, each player gets both Tractor Beams and Shield "
"Projectors, but use the higher values for Ship Size, ships checked off, "
"and cost to research Ship Size 7."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1117
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Advanced Destroyers</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1118
msgid "All DDs are DDX. Replicators get +1 RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1124
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Battlecarrier Universica</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1125
msgid ""
"BVs can be built as soon as Fighter 2 tech is researched. Replicators get"
" +1 RP at start. Do not use (draw another card) if an Alternate Empire is"
" in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1131
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Raiders</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1132
msgid ""
"All Raiders are Raider Xs (38.9), but each player gets Scanner 2 for free"
" the moment Scanner 1 is researched (buying Scanner 1 allows you to "
"detect all raiders). NPAs with Scanners still only have Scanner 1. "
"Replicators get +1 RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1138
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Advanced Bases</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1139
msgid ""
"All players may build Advanced Bases (38.4) at start. Replicators get +1 "
"RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1145
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Tough Planets</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1147
msgid "Planetary Defense Strength from Ground Units present is doubled."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1148
msgid ""
"EXAMPLE: if 4 Ground Units are present, the planet has a Defense Strength"
" of 4 and not 2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1149
msgid "Ships attacking Replicator colonies get -1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1156
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Tough Shipyards</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1157
msgid ""
"All Shipyards, regardless of Empire Advantage, have Hull Size 2 (C3-0-2) "
"and can mount Attack 2 and Defense 2 technology. Maintenance and all "
"other SY rules remain the same. When this is in play, the Empire "
"Advantage <span class=\"text-uppercase\">On the Move #58</span> can't be "
"used. Replicators get +1 RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1163
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Stealth Transports</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1164
msgid ""
"If no type of Base or Defense Satellite Network is present, Ground Units "
"can be landed before resolving space combat or after any round during "
"which the Base or DSN that prevented landing was destroyed. <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Ion Cannons #134</span> do not prevent the early "
"landing of Ground Units."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1170
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Ion Cannons</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1171
msgid ""
"All player Colonies are equipped with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Ion "
"Cannons</span>. Similar to the Militia counter, the Ion Cannon counter is"
" added to the defending force for space combat. There is no penalty for "
"their destruction. They do not benefit from nor provide rolls for "
"experience. A Colony, regardless of size (even a new one), will have 3 "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Ion Cannons</span>. Even if destroyed, "
"there will be three available at the start of the next combat. These "
"count towards the Fleet Size Bonus and automatically upgrade tech to the "
"limit of their Hull Size (similar to a Base). No maintenance cost needs "
"to be paid for the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Ion Cannons</span> and "
"they cannot be boarded. They are A5-0-x1 regardless of Empire Advantage."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1177
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">We Need the White</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1178
msgid ""
"At the start of the 6th Econ Phase, each player selects their Home System"
" Colony that is farthest in hexes from their Homeworld. If there is a "
"tie, each player may choose between their own tied colonies. Mark that "
"colony with a Key Planet counter. If that Colony is ever destroyed or "
"captured, that player loses the game (as if they lost their Homeworld)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1184
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Doomsday Machines</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1185
msgid ""
"Whenever a Doomsday Machine (29.0) is discovered in Deep Space it attacks"
" the ship that discovered it. If Exploration Technology (9.8) was used, "
"the DM is revealed and placed in the hex with the ship that discovered "
"it; ships in that hex cannot move that turn and no other ships may enter "
"that hex. If the DM survives the battle it will move one hex per turn by "
"the fastest route to attack the Homeworld of the player that discovered "
"it. It will remove planets and Asteroids along the way. If two hexes are "
"equidistant to the Homeworld, determine randomly which one it will enter."
" It will avoid moving into a hex with combat-capable ships and Bases if "
"doing so does not increase the number of hexes to reach the Homeworld. "
"<i>Warning: This drastically changes the game. It is a real danger to "
"explore Deep Space when this is in effect.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1191
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Space Amoebas</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1192
msgid "Play according to the rules for the Space Amoeba scenario (CSB 10.0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1198
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Heavy Terrain</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1200
msgid ""
"Place 2 System markers in each Deep Space hex. If there are not enough "
"markers to do this, place them so that they evenly cover rows between the"
" players starting in the center. For example, if there were 6 rows of "
"Deep Space between the players and there was only enough to cover 5 rows,"
" then only the center 4 rows of Deep Space get a second marker. Both are "
"revealed and explored simultaneously (If using Exploration Technology "
"both are looked at simultaneously by one ship and it is not possible to "
"reveal only one marker). If a Super Nova or Fold in Space is revealed, "
"then remove the other marker. If a hex has both a Super Nova and a Fold "
"in Space, remove the Fold in Space. If a Cosmic Storm (25.1) is flipped, "
"remove it if the other marker is something a Storm cannot enter. "
"Otherwise, if there are two permanent terrain markers, they both remain. "
"Use the terrain tile from one of them and put the other counter on top of"
" it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1201
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: If an Asteroid and Nebula were revealed in the same hex, then"
" everyone fires as E-Class; there is no Cloak, no Attack Tech, and no "
"Defense Tech.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1208
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Safer Space</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1209
msgid ""
"Whenever a Danger! marker is flipped, one die is rolled for each ship in "
"that hex. They are only eliminated on a roll of 7-10. On a roll of 1-6, "
"there is no effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1215
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Smart Scientists</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1216
msgid ""
"The research cost of all technologies is decreased by 5 CP before any "
"Empire Advantage is applied. Replicators also get +1 RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1222
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Trained Defenders</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1223
msgid ""
"When invaded, every Colony gets 2 Heavy Infantry Militia in addition to "
"any other Militia or Ground Units from other sources. These two are "
"represented by a separate HI counter and are removed at the end of ground"
" combat, regardless of who wins (All other HI is targeted first i.e. at "
"the end of combat remove 2 HI or 1 if it's the only HI left. No effect if"
" no HI are left at the end of combat). Do not use (draw another card) if "
"Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1229
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Know the Weakness</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1230
msgid ""
"All Unique Ships are equipped with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Design "
"Weakness</span> ability. However, instead of giving modifiers against the"
" randomly rolled ship type, the Unique Ships get +2 against the randomly "
"rolled ship type. Roll on the usual table when a UN from a given player "
"first enters combat to determine the ship type. There are no cost savings"
" for Unique Ships having this installed and it does not count towards the"
" other techs they can have installed. The standard version of <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Design Weakness</span> cannot be chosen when using "
"this Scenario Modifier. Discard and draw another card if not playing with"
" Unique Ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1236
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">No Temporal Prime Directive</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1237
msgid ""
"When spending Temporal Points (36.6), everything costs half of normal "
"(rounded up). Discard and draw another card if not playing with "
"Facilities. <i>Beware End of Empire!</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1243
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Bloody Combat</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1244
msgid "All units except Ground Units have their Attack Strength increased by one."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1250
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Experienced Crew</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1251
msgid ""
"At the start of the game, all Players draw 6 Crew Cards (12.0) and keep "
"3. Set them aside. These Crew are held in reserve and not assigned to a "
"group until the player chooses to do so. They can only be assigned to a "
"newly built group during an Economic Phase. No other Crew Cards are used "
"in this game (except if drawn by Resource Card)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1257
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Life is Complicated</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1258
msgid ""
"Discard this card and draw 2 in its place. A total of 3 Scenario Modifier"
" Cards will be in effect for this game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1264
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Rich Minerals</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1265
msgid ""
"The income from all Minerals is doubled. If Minerals +5/-3 is being used "
"to change the value of the Mineral, that change happens before the "
"doubling."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1271
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Technology Head Start</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1272
msgid ""
"Each player starts the game with 75 CP that can only be spent on "
"technology. This is spent before receiving starting units so it is "
"possible that a player's original units may start with additional "
"technology. No more than two levels of Ship Size or Movement tech and no "
"more than one level of any other tech may be purchased at start. Up to 10"
" of these CP may be carried over into the start of the game (and used as "
"normal CP in the game) - if playing with Facilities, these are RP and not"
" CP. Do not use (draw another card) if Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1278
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Low Maintenance</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1279
msgid ""
"All maintenance costs are halved. When calculating maintenance, add up "
"the total maintenance cost that you would normally pay (including "
"modifiers from e.g. experience) and then divide it in half (rounded "
"down). When tracking the change in maintenance on the Production Sheet, "
"extra notes will have to be kept on the pre-halved value to prevent "
"having to recount all of your maintenance costs every Economic Phase. If "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Robot Race #190</span> is being used, that"
" player would pay no maintenance. Do not use (draw another card) if "
"Replicators are in the game."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1285
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Where No Man Has Gone Before</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1289
msgid ""
"This card may only be played during your turn. This card may be played "
"face up in front of a player while there are still unexplored Deep Space "
"System markers. Every player's ship with Exploration tech may explore "
"twice each turn. Once every Deep Space System marker is revealed, (only) "
"the player who played this card gets to roll on the Mission Benefit "
"Table."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1296
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Time Travel Slingshot</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1300
msgid ""
"Play when one of your CAs performs a Black Hole Slingshot in Deep Space "
"without being destroyed. Leave this card face up. Discard it to reveal "
"all enemy groups/counters in one hex that could be moved into by at least"
" one of your combat-capable ships."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1307
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Journey to Babel</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1311
msgid ""
"Play when one of your CAs moves by itself into the same hex as an "
"unconquered Deep Space NPA Planet; it has picked up a diplomatic "
"delegation. Instead of a normal battle, one random NPA ship from the "
"planet attacks the CA, which may not retreat. The NPA ship is on a "
"suicide mission and gets +1 attack and defense. Regardless of the "
"outcome, the NPA ship is eliminated. Any other NPA ships at that planet "
"will not attack the CA. The CA must leave the hex next turn. If the CA "
"defeats the ship and reaches its Homeworld, in the following Economic "
"Phase the NPA Planet (if still unconquered) becomes allies to that player"
" as if they had the Empire Advantage <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Amazing Diplomats #48</span>. Place a 5 CP colony on that "
"planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1318
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Balance of Terror</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1322
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select one other player. The two players each "
"select one of their ships (a Group may be split to facilitate this) "
"located in Deep Space, regardless of each ship's location in relation to "
"one another. If a player has no ships in Deep Space, they may choose any "
"one of their ships. If the ship can carry fighters and has fighters in "
"the same hex, up to the amount of fighters the ship may carry are chosen "
"too. These two chosen units then have an immediate battle to the death in"
" open space with no possibility of retreat. The winner of this battle may"
" attack a hex with a colony belonging to a player involved in the battle "
"(not a Homeworld) with the chosen units regardless of location. After the"
" attack and any possible bombardment, the units are returned to their "
"previous hex if they survive. The Temporal Engine Benefit <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Temporal Maneuver</span> may not be used during this "
"Mission."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1329
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Creature from Below</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1333
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select a non-Homeworld Colony in a Home System, "
"friendly or enemy, and place the Creature token (A5-2-x4, 3 attacks each "
"round) on it. This Creature does no damage to the planet, but the Colony "
"is treated as if it is blockaded until the Creature is defeated in ground"
" combat (Militia do not participate). Troops on the same planet must "
"attack the Creature during their owner's next combat phase. If the "
"Creature defeats the Troops, all damage to it is healed and the Colony is"
" still considered blockaded. When it is defeated, that player gets a one-"
"time bonus of 15 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1340
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Arena</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1344
msgid ""
"Play at the start of a battle involving exactly one ship of each side. An"
" advanced entity stops the battle and decides it is more civilized to "
"have the captains of each ship fight to the death <i>(how that is "
"actually more advanced or civilized is unclear)</i>. Regardless of the "
"ships involved, the player that played the card wins the battle on a roll"
" of 1-6, their opponent on a roll of 7-10. The ship on the losing side is"
" destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1351
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Difficult Planet Survey</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1355
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select any planet without a Colony or NPAs and "
"mark it with the Difficult Survey counter. This planet is difficult to "
"settle. Every time at least one CA or Flagship ends its turn in the "
"planet's hex, roll a die. On a roll of a 1-2, the marker is taken by the "
"owner of the ships, and the planet may be colonized. If the colony is "
"placed by the player with the counter they draw 1 Alien Tech card and "
"keep it. This is in addition to any other Alien Tech drawn for colonizing"
" the planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1362
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Easy Planet Survey</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1366
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select any planet without a colony or Non-Player "
"Aliens and mark it with the Easy Survey counter. It cannot be colonized "
"unless 2 SCs are in the same hex at the time the Colony Ship lands. When "
"colonized, this planet will grow 2 steps (instead of 1) during the next "
"Economic Phase, then remove the counter."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1373
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Scientific Survey</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1377
msgid ""
"Play this card face up when one of your CAs is adjacent to a Super Nova. "
"Turn the CA face up. If this CA subsequently moves adjacent to 2 other "
"Super Novas, discard this card and roll on the Mission Benefit Table. If "
"the player turns the CA face down at a Colony or if it is destroyed, "
"discard this card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1384
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Stellar Anomaly Investigation</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1388
msgid ""
"Play this card face up when you have 2 of your combat ships of different "
"types in the same Deep Space hex containing at least one Nebula marker. "
"Turn those ships face up. At the end of each turn (including this one), "
"roll the die. On a roll of 1-3, discard this card and roll on the Mission"
" Benefit Table. If one or both ships leave the hex discard this card for "
"no effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1395
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Distress Call</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1399
msgid ""
"Play when a ship you control is eliminated in battle. Instead of being "
"destroyed, it is placed in a hex adjacent to the battle that is farther "
"from your Homeworld than the battle hex (your choice). The chosen hex "
"must contain one or more unexplored system markers if possible. When this"
" hex is explored, remove and ignore the system markers. The player cannot"
" move this ship until the turn after another of their ships ends their "
"turn in the hex, but the ship may defend itself normally. This card may "
"be played on a ship that had the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Play Dead"
" #102</span> Resource Card played on it if you lose the battle and that "
"ship is going to be destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1406
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Quell Riots</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1411
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select a non-Homeworld Colony in a Home System, "
"friendly or enemy, and mark it with the Riot counter. While the counter "
"is at the Colony it is considered blockaded. If at least 4 Hull Points "
"worth of combat-capable units except Shipyards, any Bases, and Defense "
"Satellite Networks belonging to the Colony's owner end their move at that"
" Colony that player rolls a die (reveal all combat-capable units involved"
" to prove it):"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1412
msgid ""
"• 1-5 – Remove Riot counter and roll twice on the Mission Benefit Table. "
"The counter remains until this result is rolled."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1413
msgid "• 6-8 – No effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1414
msgid ""
"• 9-10 – Reduce Colony one step. This can reduce the Colony to start, but"
" never destroy it."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1415
msgid ""
"If less than 4 Hull Points worth of ships are at the Colony during an "
"Economic Phase, roll the die but there is only an effect on 9-10 as per "
"above. This counts any modifiers to hull size, e.g. <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Giant Race #34</span> and <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Insectoids #43</span>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1423
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Police State</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1427
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select a Deep Space Colony, friendly or enemy, and"
" mark it with the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Police State</span> "
"counter. Very valuable resources have been discovered on this planet, but"
" the indigenous population does not want to make them available. The "
"Colony is considered blockaded unless the owner has at least 4 Space "
"Marines and/or Heavy Infantry and 6 Hull Points of combat-capable units "
"(including Bases, Shipyards, DSN) revealed in that hex (This counts any "
"modifiers to hull size, e.g. <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Giant Race "
"#34</span> and <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Insectoids #43</span>). If "
"they do, the Colony produces 10 additional CP that Economic Phase. If "
"playing with Facilities (36.0), the additional income is always CP "
"regardless of the Facility present. As soon as less than required units "
"are present the colony is considered blockaded again."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1434
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">New FTL Test</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1439
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Reveal a ship with at least 2 Hull Points in Deep "
"Space in a hex with no other ships. It must have the highest level of "
"Movement Technology that you have researched. The Technology Level does "
"not need to be revealed. Roll a die one time:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1440
msgid ""
"• 1-7 – The test is a success! The next Movement technology purchased is "
"discounted by 15 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1441
msgid "• 8-9 – The test fails."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1442
msgid "• 10 – Calamity! The test ship is destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1450
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Dimensional Anomaly</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1454
msgid ""
"Play during your Exploration Phase when a CA is your only ship (not "
"Group) in a hex that had a system marker explored by that CA this phase "
"(after resolving any system marker effects, including combat against "
"NPAs) The CA is then shifted to another dimension and is removed from the"
" board. At the beginning of each Economic Phase, roll a die. On 1-3, the "
"CA is placed back on the board at a friendly Base or Shipyard. Subtract 2"
" from the die roll for each successive Econ Phase (e.g., in the third "
"Econ Phase it would be -4 to the roll). The CA does not pay maintenance "
"while off board. Roll on Mission Benefit Table when it returns to the "
"board. System marker may have been previously peeked at (but not "
"flipped), using Exploration technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1461
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Asteroid Strike</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1465
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Place the Rogue Asteroid counter in an Asteroid "
"hex and place the Asteroid Target counter in the same hex as an enemy "
"non-Homeworld Colony at least two hexes away. Each Economic Phase the "
"Rogue Asteroid moves one hex closer to the Colony (your choice if two "
"hexes are equidistant). If it enters the same hex as the Colony, remove "
"both the Colony and the Rogue Asteroid. If any player ends the movement "
"phase in the same hex as the Rogue Asteroid with ships that have a "
"combined Attack Strength of 3 or more (not counting attack technology), "
"the player may remove the Rogue Asteroid counter (being in a hex when the"
" Rogue Asteroid moves into the hex is not sufficient). Boarding Ships "
"count as having an Attack Strength of 1 for this, Missile Boats count as "
"having an Attack Strength of 6. If the units in the hex do not have a "
"combined total of at least 3 Attack Strength, nothing happens."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1472
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Urgent Deep Space Survey</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1476
msgid ""
"Play when one of your ships that is worth 12+ CP ends its turn in one of "
"the following types of terrain in Deep Space – Nebula, Asteroids, Black "
"Hole, Warp Point, Plasma Storm, Ion Storm, Quantum Filament, Quasar, or "
"Pulsar. The ship must then subsequently end its turn in 3 more of the "
"listed terrain types (it must be different hexes, but not necessarily "
"different terrain types) and then get back to one of your Colonies that "
"has a Shipyard, Base, or Starbase. If successful, roll on the Mission "
"Benefit Table. The ship performing this Mission must be revealed when the"
" card is played. You may use your Flagship to complete this mission. If "
"the designated ship is destroyed or the ship is flipped face down, "
"discard this card."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1483
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Survivors</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1487
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. A shuttle containing one of your enemy's people "
"(choose an opponent at random) has crash-landed on a revealed but "
"uncolonized NPA planet (choose randomly). Mark the planet with a counter "
"from that Empire. If you colonize the planet while it has the counter you"
" capture the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">survivors</span> and ransom "
"them back for 10 CP (gained by you as if it was mineral income and lost "
"by that enemy during the next Economic Phase) and get to look at the "
"technology portion of that Empire's Production Sheet (immediately) and "
"the counter is removed. If another player colonizes this planet, the "
"counter is removed without any effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1494
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Sins of the Father</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1498
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select one of your ships of Hull Size 2 or greater"
" in a Deep Space hex. A crew member from that ship must resolve a "
"familial dispute on your Homeworld. If this ship begins and ends a turn "
"at the Homeworld, draw a Crew Card (12.0). Do this even if not playing "
"with Crew Cards. The Crew Card must be played as normal during the next "
"Economic Phase or is discarded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1505
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Defend an Outpost</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1509
msgid ""
"Play at the end of your turn. Choose one of your own non-Homeworld Deep "
"Space Colonies. The opponent of your choice MUST immediately attack it "
"with between 2 and 10 of their Ground Units (if possible). These Ground "
"Units can be taken from anywhere on the board, including Transports, and "
"are instantly placed on the planet and may fire normally during the first"
" round (unlike normal rules, 21.8.3). The defender does not get Militia. "
"There is no space battle, but all units in the hex are revealed. If the "
"attacker wins, they may decide to capture this Colony by removing one "
"surviving Ground Unit as normal. If the defender (the person that played "
"the card) wins the attack, they roll on the Mission Benefit Table. If the"
" player chosen does not have at least 2 Ground Units, no attack takes "
"place, and the defender gets to roll on the Mission Benefit Table."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1527
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Minerals +5/–3</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1538
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Privateers</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1543
msgid "Can be played for one of two effects:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1544
msgid ""
"• Play when peeking at a Space Pirate using Exploration Technology or "
"Regional Map to hire that Space Pirate as if the counter was revealed "
"during the Exploration Phase. In the case of using Exploration "
"technology, the Space Pirate is hired before movement and may therefore "
"be moved under the player's control that turn."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1545
msgid ""
"• Play when revealing a Space Pirate during the Exploration Phase while "
"already in control of a Space Pirate to ignore the restriction and hire "
"the newly revealed Space Pirate as normal."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1553
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Hidden Power</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1564
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Virus</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1568
msgid ""
"Play during your turn. Select any non-Homeworld Colony. Place a <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Virus</span> counter on it. In the next Economic"
" Phase, that Colony is treated as if it is blockaded. Remove the counter "
"at the end of that Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1575
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Sabotage</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1579
msgid ""
"Play at the beginning of your first turn after an Economic Phase. A "
"player of your choice must destroy one Defense Satellite Network or any "
"type of Base of their own choice. Replicators must destroy one ship not "
"in their Home System. If the player does not have one of those, then this"
" card is discarded for no effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1586
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Population +/-</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1590
msgid ""
"Play during an Economic Phase after adjusting Colony income. Choose one "
"non-Homeworld Colony. That Colony either grows an extra level or goes "
"down one level. This cannot cause a Colony to be eliminated but can "
"reduce it to 0."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1597
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Self-Sustaining Power Source</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1598
msgid "Titans pay 1/2 maintenance (round down the total)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1605
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Advanced Shipyards</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1606
msgid ""
"Shipyards produce an extra half Hull Point each. (1.5 at level one, 2 at "
"level 2, 2.5 at level three.)"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1613
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Lorelei System</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1614
msgid ""
"Allows a player to designate their SC, SCX, DD, and DDX as the target of "
"Mines that were not swept after technology was revealed in combat "
"(17.1.3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1621
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Ancient Weapons Cache</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1622
msgid ""
"In the following Economic Phase, the player gains 2 Cyber Armor (38.7) at"
" one of their Colonies even if they do not have the appropriate "
"technology."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1624
msgid "When any Cyber Armor is revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1629
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Quantum Computing</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1630
msgid ""
"All of this player's Unique Ships may now mount a 3rd Unique Technology "
"and they no longer pay 5 CP to redesign UNs. Immediately add a 3rd tech "
"to your current UN design (do not change any other aspect). All UNs "
"currently on the board gain this third tech (at your current tech level "
"if applicable) at no cost."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1632
msgid "When gained."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1637
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Focused Phasers</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1638
msgid "Unique Ships get +1 to their Attack Strength."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1640 app/data/cards.py:2119 app/data/cards.py:2129
msgid "When a UN is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1645
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Skipper Missiles</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1646
msgid "All Missiles (24.4) strike their targets as C-Class instead of E-Class."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1648
msgid "When a MB is present in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1653
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">War Sun</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1654
msgid ""
"This race has spent generations refitting an ancient warship, and it is "
"nearly operational. Once during the game, they gain a free Titan at their"
" Homeworld. It will have the player's current tech and requires no "
"Shipyard to place. It pays no maintenance as long as it is at a friendly "
"Colony during the Econ Phase. <strong>This ship may not enter Deep Space "
"until Ship Size 6 has been researched.</strong> Additionally, the <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">War Sun</span> has revealed to this race the "
"ability to pass safely through Super Nova hexes (though they cannot end "
"their movement in one). Alternate Empires (24.0) are given one Titan "
"counter. This is the only time an Alternate Empire can have a Titan; they"
" may still not research or build other Titans and they may not rebuild "
"this one if destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1656
msgid "This ship may not enter Deep Space until Ship Size 6 has been researched."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1658
msgid "When any of their Titan counters are revealed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1663
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Salvage Experts</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1664
msgid ""
"When this race wins a space battle, they may salvage one "
"<strong><i>friendly</i></strong> destroyed combat ship (not Shipyards, "
"Bases, Mines, Starbases, Defense Satellite Networks, or Flagships). The "
"salvaged ship is placed face down in the hex at its previous Ship "
"Experience level. Ships that were carrying other units or Logistic Points"
" when they were destroyed do not regain them when the ship is salvaged. "
"If none of their ships are destroyed no ship is gained, but if the enemy "
"lost at least one combat ship, this empire gains 3 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1666
msgid "When first entering combat, including Aliens."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1671
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Berserker Genome</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1672
msgid ""
"At the end of every combat round of space combat in which this race loses"
" a unit, they may make a special attack for each unit destroyed (units "
"hit by boarding attacks do not count as destroyed for this purpose). "
"These bonus attacks hit on a roll of 1+the Hull Size of the destroyed "
"unit, regardless of the target's defense and does one damage (example: a "
"destroyed BC gets a final attack hitting on 1-3)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1679
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Robot Race</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1680
msgid ""
"Due to the low maintenance of this race, all maintenance is halved; add "
"up all maintenance costs (including reductions from alien technology "
"cards and experience), divide the total in half and round down."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1687
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Masters of the Gates</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1688
msgid ""
"All CAs have <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Warp Gates</span> without any"
" research and at no extra cost. Rules as per UN Ship Table 3."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1690
msgid "The first time a Warp Gate is used or a CA is in combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1695
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Mycroft</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1696
msgid ""
"Natural attack rolls of \"1\" by ships in this Group grant the attacking "
"ship a second attack roll (these may be against the same or different "
"Groups). If on a ship with Hull Size of 1, the second attack roll is "
"granted on rolls of 1-2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1702
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Hive Queen</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1703
msgid ""
"This Group gets +1 Defense Strength. All OTHER Replicator Groups in the "
"fleet get +1 Attack Strength and -1 Defense Strength. This is not "
"optional!"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1709
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Hal 10K</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1710
msgid ""
"This Group fires at its normal Weapon class, regardless of terrain. "
"Movement Rules are unaffected by this."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1716
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">ROMmie</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1717
msgid ""
"Every time a ship in this Group suffers a hit, roll a die. On a roll of "
"1, the hit is ignored."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1723
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">WOPR</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1724
msgid ""
"Once per round, this Group may reroll one Attack die or choose one Attack"
" die against the Group to be rerolled. The decision must be made "
"immediately after the die is rolled. The first result is undone and the "
"second roll must be used."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1730
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Data</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1731
msgid ""
"During movement only, this Group ignores Asteroids, Nebulae, and Black "
"Holes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1737
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Skynet</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1738
msgid ""
"During the first round of combat only, this Group and 2 others of the "
"Replicator player's choice fight as one Weapon Class higher."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1744
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Quorra</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1745
msgid ""
"This Group cannot be targeted by Mines as if equipped with <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Anti-Sensor Hull</span>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1751
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Agent Smith</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1752
msgid ""
"This fleet gets a Fleet Size Bonus when it has at least one more combat-"
"capable ship than the opponent. The opposing fleet does not get a Fleet "
"Size Bonus unless this Crew Card's fleet is outnumbered by 3:1. If the "
"opposing fleet is <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Expert Tacticians "
"#45</span> or has an <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Admiral Of The Navy "
"#245 #246</span> (or both), everything cancels each other out and the "
"Fleet Size Bonus is given at 2:1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1758
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Ash</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1759
msgid ""
"In each combat, choose one hex into which the enemy cannot retreat. The "
"decision of which hex is forbidden is made when an enemy Group announces "
"intent to retreat for the first time and applies to all enemy retreats in"
" that combat. The restriction is immediately lifted if this Group is "
"destroyed or retreats. The Group may be screened and still take advantage"
" of this effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1765
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Alexa</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1766
msgid ""
"This Group's Movement technology operates as if it was one level higher "
"than currently installed, even if that higher level has not been "
"researched. It can't operate at a level above the maximum of Movement 7."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1772
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Sonny</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1773 app/data/cards.py:1808
msgid ""
"One ship in this Group gets +1 to Attack Strength. If on a Group with a "
"Hull Size of 1, it gets +2 and ignores the first hit against it in "
"combat."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1779
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Governor</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1780
msgid ""
"The Group gets 2 attacks in the first combat round only. If on a Flagship"
" or Titan, this applies to all combat rounds. If on a Titan, each hit "
"from the Group also does 3 Damage, but every time a ship in the Group is "
"hit by a fighter, roll a die. On a roll of 10 a Titan is destroyed."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1786
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Security Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1787
msgid ""
"Regardless of whether the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Security "
"Officer</span> survives, all friendly crew in the same Fleet as this "
"officer get -2 to <strong><i>all</i></strong> survival rolls. All ships "
"in the Group get +1 defense against Boarding Ships. If on a Flagship, "
"select one additional Group at the beginning of combat that will receive "
"this benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1793
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Damage Control Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1794
msgid ""
"If this Group has any damage, after each round of combat it may attempt "
"repairs. On a roll of a 1 or less, repair all damage. On a roll of a 2-5,"
" repair 1 Damage. If on the Flagship or a BB, subtract 2 from the die "
"roll."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1800
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Ensign Expendable</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1801
msgid "This Crew Card can be discarded to cancel one hit against this Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1807
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Hero</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1814
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Engineer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1815
msgid ""
"This Group's Movement Tech operates at one level higher than currently "
"installed, even if that higher level has not been researched. It can't "
"operate at a level above the maximum of 7."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1821
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Asteroid Navigator</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1822
msgid ""
"This Group can ignore Asteroids when moving. If playing with <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Thick Asteroids #117</span>, this Group does not take"
" damage from the Asteroids. If on a SC, DD, or Flagship, it also ignores "
"Black Holes (unless using Slingshot)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1828
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Nebula Navigator</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1829
msgid ""
"This Group can ignore Nebulae when moving. If on a SC, DD, or the "
"Flagship, it may also ignore Black Holes (unless using Slingshot, 31.0). "
"If on a MB, it also ignores Asteroids when moving."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1835
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Helmsmen</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1836
msgid ""
"This Group may fire and then immediately retreat in the same round (they "
"may still not retreat on round 1 unless permitted by some other effect). "
"If on a Raider, the Group may also fire and retreat in round 1. The group"
" retreats prior to any other effects e.g. <span class=\"text-uppercase\">"
" #110</span>."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1842
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Supply Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1843
msgid ""
"Each ship in the Group pays 1 less maintenance. This is applied prior to "
"any other reductions due to experience, alien technologies, empire "
"advantages, etc."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1849
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Defender</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1850
msgid ""
"Once per battle, after the first round, at the start of a round, this "
"Group may announce that it is setting its defenses to \"Area Mode.\" For "
"that round, or until all ships in this Group are destroyed, all attacks "
"against other friendly Groups suffer an additional penalty equal to the "
"defense technology of the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Defender</span> "
"Group (if in a Nebula, this would be zero). However, attacks against the "
"<span class=\"text-uppercase\">Defender</span> Group suffer no penalty "
"due to its defense technology. This may be used even if the Group is "
"screened. If on a BC, this benefit may be used in the first round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1856
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Tactician</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1857
msgid ""
"After the first round, during a single round of combat, if your fleet in "
"the combat contains Groups of at least three different Hull Sizes, your "
"ships gain +1 Attack or +1 Defense for the round. This bonus is "
"determined at the start of the round and stays in effect even if all "
"ships of one hull size are destroyed partway through the round. If on a "
"BB or DN, this benefit may be used in the first round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1863
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Strategist</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1864
msgid ""
"Once in each combat, choose four enemy ships (not Groups) and decide "
"which one of your Groups they will fire against in that round. If that "
"Group is destroyed, they are free to choose their next target. The "
"designated Group must be a legal target (not a CV with Fighters, etc.). "
"If on a SC, DD, CA, or MB, six enemy ships may be chosen in that round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1872
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">First Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1873
msgid ""
"This Group gets +2 to its Tactics level (to a max of 3). If on an SC or a"
" DD, this Group also improves its Weapon Class by one letter, even in "
"terrain (SC would fire as D-Class in Asteroids, etc.). This is in "
"addition to any other benefits like <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Longbowmen #59</span> or <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Long "
"Lance Torpedo #5</span>. If on the Flagship, this ship always fires or "
"retreats before all other ships in the combat, regardless of technology "
"or terrain."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1879
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Tactical Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1880
msgid ""
"Once during each battle, this ship (not Group) may fire (or retreat if "
"eligible) as A-Class, even in terrain. If on an SC or DD this applies to "
"the entire Group. All ships in the Group get +1 to defense against "
"boarding. If on a Flagship, this applies to one other group as well."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1886
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Captain</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1887
msgid ""
"May reroll one attack from the Group or have one attack against it "
"rerolled once per combat round. The decision must be made immediately "
"after the die is rolled. The first result is undone and the second roll "
"must be used. If on an SC, DD, CA, or MB, it may reroll 2 attacks per "
"round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1893
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Weapons Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1894
msgid ""
"Natural attack rolls of 1 by ships in this Group grant the attacking ship"
" a second attack roll (against the same or a different Group as the first"
" attack). If on an SC, DD, Raider, or Flagship, the second attack roll is"
" granted on 1 or 2."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1900
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Heavy Weapons Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1901
msgid ""
"All ships in this Group do 2 damage every time they hit a Colony, any "
"type of Base, Shipyard, or Defense Satellite Network."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1907
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Science Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1908
msgid ""
"This Group cannot be targeted by Mines in the same way as <span class"
"=\"text-uppercase\">Anti-Sensor Hull</span>. If on a SW, this Group also "
"sweeps one more Mine per ship."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1914
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Marine Captain</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1915
msgid ""
"The Group can carry one extra Ground Unit total even if it normally could"
" not carry Ground Units. If on a CA, each ship in the Group can carry one"
" Ground Unit. If on a Flagship, the Group may carry 4 Ground Units total."
" Ships in the Group carrying Ground Units cannot be boarded."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1921
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Planetary Admiral</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1922
msgid ""
"Group gets +1 Attack Strength if fighting in a hex with a planet. If on a"
" BB, DN, or Titan, all ships in the fleet get this bonus."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1928
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Admiral of the Navy</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1929
msgid ""
"This fleet gets a Fleet Size Bonus when it has at least one more combat-"
"capable ship than the opponent. The opposing fleet does not get a Fleet "
"Size Bonus unless this Crew Card's fleet is outnumbered by 3:1. If the "
"opposing fleet is <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Expert Tacticians "
"#45</span> or has <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Agent Smith #200</span> "
"or has an <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Admiral of the Navy</span> (or "
"any combination thereof), everything cancels each other out and the Fleet"
" Size Bonus is given at 2:1."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1935
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Fleet Admiral</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1936
msgid ""
"This Group and 2 others get +1 Attack on the first round of combat only. "
"If on a Titan, then one additional Group gets this benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1942
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Admiral</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1943
msgid ""
"This Group and 2 others fight as one Weapon Class higher for the first "
"round of combat only. If on a DN, then one additional Group gets this "
"benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1949
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Commander</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1950
msgid ""
"If this fleet has more ships than the opponent, it can designate one "
"Group in this fleet that cannot be shot at the first round unless all "
"other ships are destroyed (i.e., for target selection treat one Group as "
"if they were a Carrier with unscreened fighters the first round). If on a"
" BB, then one additional Group gets this benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1958
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Rear Admiral</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1959
msgid ""
"This Group and 1 other have their Defense Strength increased by one for "
"the first round of combat only. If on a DN, then one additional Group "
"gets this benefit."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1965
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">General Staff</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1966
msgid ""
"In each combat, this Crew can choose one hex that the enemy can't retreat"
" into as long as the <span class=\"text-uppercase\">General "
"Staff</span>'s Group is in the combat. The decision of which hex is "
"forbidden is made when an enemy Group announces intent to retreat for the"
" first time and applies to all enemy retreats in that combat. The "
"restriction is immediately lifted if this Group is destroyed or retreats."
" The Group may be screened and still take advantage of this effect."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1972
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Ordnance Technician/ECCM Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1973
msgid ""
"If on a CV or BV, all Fighters in the same fleet that would fire as "
"B-Class fire instead as A-Class. If on an MB, when this Group fires on "
"CAs with Jamming Technology, the Missiles ignore all jamming. On any "
"Group other than CV, BV or MB, this Crew Card can be discarded to cancel "
"one hit against the Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1979
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Warrant Officer/ECCM Specialist</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1980
msgid ""
"If on a CV or BV, ships in this Group can carry 1 extra Fighter each. If "
"on an MB, all ships in this Group may fire ECCM Missiles instead of using"
" their normal attack. These Missiles do no damage and do not attack enemy"
" ships. For each ship that fires ECCM Missiles each round, two Missiles "
"fired by other MBs ignore all jamming. On any Group other than CV, BV or "
"MB, this Crew Card can be discarded to cancel one hit against this Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1986
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Squadron Leader</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1987
msgid ""
"Ships in this Group get +1 Attack Strength. If on a Fighter, the ships in"
" this Group also get +1 Defense Strength and fire as A-Class (regardless "
"of terrain)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1993
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">CAG</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:1994
msgid ""
"If on a CV or BV, one Group of Fighters in the fleet fires as A-Class and"
" gets +1 Attack Strength each round, regardless of terrain. A different "
"Group may be chosen each round. On any group other than CV or BV, this "
"Crew Card can be discarded to cancel one hit against this Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2000
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Deck Crew Chief</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2001
msgid ""
"If on a CV or BV, at the end of a round of combat, roll a die. On a roll "
"of a 1-4, one friendly Fighter that was destroyed that round is returned "
"to service (no benefit if no fighter was destroyed that round). If on a "
"BV, subtract 3 from the roll. If playing with Experience, the Fighters "
"that are returned are Skilled. On any group other than CV or BV, this "
"Crew Card can be discarded to cancel one hit against this Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2007
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Gunnery Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2008
msgid ""
"Group fires at its normal Weapon Class regardless of terrain. If on a BC,"
" this applies to one other Group as well."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2014
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Commodore</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2015
msgid ""
"At the start of combat select one enemy Group. This Group cannot split "
"and cannot retreat until round 3. If on a BB, this applies to all "
"opposing Groups."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2021
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Marine Commander</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2022
msgid ""
"If on a Transport, this Group can drop Ground Units before space combat "
"starts when attacking another player (not NPAs). Ground combat is still "
"resolved after Space combat. On any group other than Transport, this Crew"
" Card can be discarded to cancel one hit against his Group."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2028
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Marine Lieutenant</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2029
msgid ""
"A Transport with this Crew Card has \"Suppressing Fire\": if this Group "
"is present in a hex where there is ground combat, pick one type of enemy "
"unit. All enemy units of that type get -2 Attack Strength on the first "
"round of ground combat. On any other ship this Crew Card can be discarded"
" to cancel one hit against this group (this discard effect cannot be used"
" on a Transport)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2035
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Special Warfare Technician</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2037
msgid ""
"This Group's Point Defense, Cloaking, Scanners, Mine Sweeping, Boarding, "
"Exploration, Missile Boat, or Jammer technologies operate as if they were"
" one level higher than currently installed, even if that technology has "
"not been researched. It cannot operate at a level above the maximum."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2038
msgid ""
"<i>EXAMPLE: A Raider with Cloaking 2 gets no benefit from this Crew "
"Card.</i>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2045
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Chief Engineer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2046
msgid "This Group gets instant technology upgrades, just like Bases or Shipyards."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2052
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Patrol Leader</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2053
msgid ""
"If a Group with this Crew Card spends its entire time between Economic "
"Phases on MS Pipelines that connect Colonies, the player gets an "
"additional 3 CP in the next Economic Phase. If this Crew Card is on a DD,"
" the player gets an additional 5 CP instead."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2059
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Astrometrics Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2060
msgid ""
"Once per Economic Phase, immediately before new ships are placed, the "
"player may peek at one face down Group belonging to another player within"
" one hex of the Group with this Crew Card. The Group remains face down "
"after peeking. If this Crew Card is on a CA, it may peek at a Group "
"within three hexes."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2066
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Operations Officer</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2068
msgid ""
"Once between Economic Phases, the Group with this Crew Card may do one of"
" the following:"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2069
msgid ""
"• Ignore the movement effect of one (and only one) hex containing Nebula,"
" Asteroids, Quantum Filament, Plasma Storm, or a Black Hole (survival is "
"automatic, but may not use Black Hole Slingshot)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2070
msgid ""
"• All ships on this Group get either +1 Attack Strength or +1 Defense "
"Strength for one round."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2071
msgid ""
"Turn this Crew Card sideways to show that it has been used and return it "
"to vertical in the next Economic Phase."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2078
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Weak NPAs</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2079
msgid ""
"All deep space Barren planets have one less ship and one less Heavy "
"Infantry (minimum 0)."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2085
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Hardy Empires</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2086
msgid "All Empires start with Terraforming 1. Replicators get +1 RP at start."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2092
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Second Salvo</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2093
msgid ""
"CAs are automatically equipped with <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Second"
" Salvo</span> at no extra cost as per the Unique Ship Rules. Prior to "
"Economic Phase 8 Flagships are treated as having <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Second Salvo</span> while in combat in the Home System of "
"their owner. After Economic Phase 8, they are automatically and "
"permanently equipped with it. Do not use (draw another card) if "
"Replicators are in the game. Do not use <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Cloaking Geniuses #50</span> if this card is in play."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2099
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Recon Ships</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2100
msgid ""
"In addition to the normal starting forces, each player receives 6 <span "
"class=\"text-uppercase\">Recon Ships</span> (use Unique Ship counters). "
"They are E1-0 x1, but cost no maintenance. They may be upgraded, but not "
"built. Do not use the normal UN rules. If a player draws Alien Tech Cards"
" 282 or 283, the player may remove any remaining <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Recon Ships</span> in order to build the new design, but may "
"not build other designs."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2106
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Bioweapons</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2107
msgid ""
"All DDs are instantly upgraded to have <span class=\"text-"
"uppercase\">Bioweapons</span>. They automatically hit when bombarding a "
"planet."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2114
msgid "<mark class=\"hl-blue\">Aegis Frigate</mark>"
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2115
msgid ""
"You have the plans to build <span class=\"text-uppercase\">Aegis "
"Frigate</span>s (use Unique Ship counters). They are E1-3 x2 and are "
"equipped with Shield Projectors (regardless of whether they have been "
"researched). They cost 11 CP."
msgstr ""

#: app/data/cards.py:2117 app/data/cards.py:2127
msgid ""
"<mark class=\"hl-green\">This card require the Unique Ship counters to "
"play. If already playing with Unique Ships, or if a Unique Ship Card is "
"already in use by this empire when a Unique Ship Card is drawn, this card"
" may be discarded to draw another. There are no Ship Size requirements "
"for Unique Ship designs given by cards.)</mark>"
